{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbc2cfe0-faff-434b-9b71-666f9cb217bd","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changed\nMTP uses `--filter` but with **MSTest-style filter expressions**, not the old VSTest syntax. The `&` operator becomes `&` or just a space, and `~` (contains) becomes `~` still but the property names differ:\n\n```\n# Old (VSTest / dotnet test)\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP)\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe filter expression itself is actually the same syntax — **but the runner changed**. With `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, `dotnet test` passes `--filter` differently. You now need either:\n\n```bash\n# Option A: dotnet test with -- passthrough syntax\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests\" --filter \"Category=Smoke\"\n\n# Option B: run the test executable directly\ndotnet run -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests\" --filter \"Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### 2. Trait filtering uses `--filter` per condition\nIn MTP, multiple `--filter` flags are **ANDed** together. The `Category=Smoke` trait filter maps to:\n\n```bash\n--filter \"trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### Your translated CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests\" --filter \"trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr if running the built executable directly:\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests\" --filter \"trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Traits use `trait=Key=Value` syntax (not just `Key=Value`)\n- Multiple `--filter` flags AND together\n- The `--` separator is required with `dotnet test` to pass MTP arguments","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"209d1bb4-f46a-4526-9a3a-29ac78dead23","outputTokens":488,"requestId":"1BDB:19BA48:1F73BBB:22E15E0:6A03CF40"},"id":"10aaa81f-0a34-4c6c-a398-00b2e76b6f6a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:09:31.904Z","parentId":"b2582061-de2f-4552-9eb8-d769cb58e431"}
